   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">This feature enables you to create a campaign with project related information.<note class="- topic/note "> Ensure all the project fields are created in the <xref href="../Settings/Application_Settings/Application_Settings.dita"
                  class="- topic/xref ">Application Settings</xref>.</note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol> page, click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create New Campaign</uicontrol> tab.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create a New Campaign</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Provide the appropriate information in the fields, as described in the following table.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <table class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Field Name </entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Description</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">CAMPAIGN TITLE</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Enter the name of the campaign.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">START DATE</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Select the start date of the campaign. The campaign starts on this date and is open to the general public to provide feedback.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">END DATE</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Select the end date of the campaign. The campaign ends on this date, and general public cannot provide feedback.<note class="- topic/note "> Based on the selected <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">START DATE</uicontrol> and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">END DATE</uicontrol>, the CAMPAIGN PERIOD(IN DAYS) field displays the number of days calculated based on the calendar dates.</note>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">DESCRIPTION</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Enter a description of the campaign explaining about the proposal and purpose of associated projects along with the supporting documents.</entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ATTACHMENTS </uicontrol>section, drag and drop files or click <image href="../Icons/Add_Icon.png"
                      class="- topic/image "
                      placement="inline"/> to browse and attach files.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note "> To provide additional details about the campaign, you can attach all supporting documents to be shared on the public platform.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click   <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Next</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add Projects</uicontrol> tab is displayed.</info>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">You can now add details of proposed projects to the campaign. To add projects to the campaign, refer to <xref href="Managing_Projects_in_a_Campaign.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Managing Projects for a New Campaign</xref>.<p class="- topic/p ">The campaign is saved in <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">DRAFT</uicontrol> status.</p>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
